    <p>COOMBE: Often, guys would press up 200, 500 copies of something that they had recorded in someone's studio basement and just, you know, scrap together enough money to put that one 45 out. Then they would drive around with it in their trunk, you know, at shows - give it to people. So it would often never even leave the area.</p>
