    <p>ADAM HOCHBERG: The proposed censure says Governor Sanford was derelict in his duties and brought dishonor, disgrace and shame upon his state. But despite that strong language, the resolution in many ways is a victory for the governor, because the legislature could've done much more. Back in the summer, when Sanford first confessed to his secret rendezvous with the woman he called his soulmate, legislative leaders talked seriously about impeaching him. Instead, Sanford is likely to escape with, at most, an ornately worded slap on the wrist.</p>
